@page "/tutorial"

<h1>Blazor Tutorial</h1>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>
<ul>
  <li>.NET 8 SDK</li>
  <li>GitHub account</li>
</ul>

<h2>1. Create the app</h2>
<pre><code>dotnet new blazorwasm -n BlazorDemo -f net8.0
cd BlazorDemo
dotnet run
</code></pre>

<h2>2. Edit a component</h2>
<p>Open <code>Pages/Counter.razor</code> and replace its contents:</p>
<pre><code>@@page "/counter"

<h1>Counter</h1>

<p>Current count: @count</p>
<button @onclick="Inc">Click me</button>

<hr />

<h2>Mini Form</h2>
<input @bind="name" placeholder="Enter your name" />
<button @onclick="Submit">Submit</button>
<p>@message</p>

@code {
    int count;
    string name = "";
    string message = "";

    void Inc() => count++;
    void Submit() => message = string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(name) ? "Please enter a name." : $"Hello, {name}!";
}
</code></pre>

<h2>3. Build for static hosting</h2>
<pre><code>dotnet publish -c Release -o publish</code></pre>

<h2>4. Run locally again</h2>
<pre><code>dotnet run</code></pre>

<h2>5. Deploy</h2>
<p>Push to the repository. GitHub Actions will publish to Pages automatically.</p>

<h2>Checks</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>/counter</code> increments instantly</li>
  <li>Form echoes the name</li>
  <li>Live site loads at <a href="https://kawrae.github.io/blazor-demo/" target="_blank">https://kawrae.github.io/blazor-demo/</a></li>
</ul>

